                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>If a silent stalker sees their own reflection or any object important to them in life, they must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:33] save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The pale stranger is unaffected and can no longer be affected by that reflection or object in this way.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The silent stalker is distracted by self-loathing and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The silent stalker becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Fascinated] by the source of their self-loathing and does everything they can to destroy it until the end of their next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The silent stalker becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Immobilized] as long as the source of their self-loathing is apparent, until they're attacked, or until they see their murderer.</p>"
